Responsibilities:
Noblis is seeking a Senior Scientist Machine Learning for their Reston headquarters location.

The Machine Learning Senior Scientist will work across Noblis as the chief scientist for research and development (R&D) in the area of machine Learning and artificial intelligence to include computer vision, AI assurance, cybersecurity, forensics, and the life sciences, among others. The Senior Scientist will work with the Chief Technology Officer (CTO) of Noblis and the executive team to develop and execute the strategy for the Machine Learning Research Center and associated internal R&D investment, while building Noblis’ machine learning-oriented new business funnel across the Federal Government. The Senior Scientist will work with Noblis' Mission Area Vice Presidents, business development, scientific researchers, and senior technical staff as well as proposal development teams to develop scientific solutions, integrate innovative approaches and technology, and incorporate feedback from Customers into current and new Noblis offerings and research.

This position reports to the Chief Technology Officer (CTO), Noblis.

The Senior Scientist, Machine Learning will

Direct the Noblis Machine Learning R&D portfolio, ensuring R&D investments align to Noblis business strategy, growth objectives, and Customer research interests;
Consult with and deliver machine learning expertise and new approaches to US Government Customers across Noblis’ Federal Civilian, Defense, Homeland Security, and National Security programs;
Collaborate with the CTO, business development, and the executive team to develop solutions and to foster relationships with Federal Government Customers to include the DoD Services, DARPA, IARPA, the Department of Energy, and the National Institutes of Health (NIH), and others;
Identify and pursue US Government-funded S&T opportunities / solicitations to include Broad Area Announcements (BAA) and Other Transaction Authorities (OTAs);
Research and develop innovative, complex, leading-edge scientific and technology solutions, applying machine learning approaches across business opportunities and multiple domain areas including various defense and national security use cases, multimedia (voice, text, imagery, video), and life sciences, and integrate research outcomes into business capture and proposal development efforts;
Drive technologies, research, and prototypes derived from Noblis’ internal research and development program into new Customer accounts in collaboration with the CTO and Mission Areas;
Work closely with scientists and technical staff (e.g., data scientists, data engineers, infrastructure engineers, and software developers) from across the company to advance the development of Noblis service and platform offerings and inform Nobis investment in scientific research;
Guide direction of and investment in the Noblis Machine Learning lab;
Develop and maintain a broad understanding of Noblis scientific, research, and technical capabilities and relay these capabilities to Customers both directly and in formal proposal submissions;
Provide demonstrations of Noblis solutions and capabilities to potential government clients;
Collaborate across diverse technology, scientific, shared service, and Customer facing organizations to engage clients and develop solutions that support their mission requirements;
Understand the needs of our Federal Civilian, Defense, and National Security markets and how to position and apply our R&D investment and solution offerings to address their requirements;
Provide overarching scientific and technical guidance to multiple concurrent programs and research projects to ensure they are on-track, on-time and meet project requirements and target outcomes:
Qualifications:
Master of Science (M.S.) degree in engineering, statistics, mathematics, computer sciences, or related field with 12+ years of experience in one or more scientific areas;
10 years specialized experience providing direct or consultant scientific support to major programs or system development efforts; experience managing scientific or technology performer work preferred at one or more US Government agencies (e.g., USAF, Army, DARPA, IARPA, DTRA, NASA, and/or the National Institutes of Health (NIH);
Previous success developing business and acquiring Government funding for scientific research and/or prototypes via BAAs, OTAs, and other solicitations; any experience with other government funding agencies should be highlighted and include a description of roles and responsibilities to demonstrate adequate experience;
Experience in applying chemical and/or biological scientific expertise to define and resolve system issues, perform analysis, and develop plans and requirements for complex systems;
Ability to coordinate multi-disciplinary research teams and manage the preparation of analysis, evaluations, and recommendations for proper implementation of programs and systems;
Possesses a scientific background or knowledge with the ability to understand scientific materials/applications/vernacular;
Excellent communication to include technical writing and editing, communicating scientific concepts to non-scientific audiences, critical thinking, and interpersonal and customer service skills to engage senior private sector and US Government personnel;
Ability to plan individual efforts and follow through to completion;
Ability to multi-task and respond to quick turn-around requests;
Competence to function efficiently in a fast-paced, demanding work environment;
Top Secret (TS) clearance, with the ability to acquire/maintain SCI, is highly preferred
DESIRED QUALIFICATIONS:
PhD or equivalent in computer science, mathematics, statistics, data science / bioinformatics, physics, or other similar scientific or engineering area
5+ years of experimental work in computer science / engineering, or a scientific field
Knowledge and understanding of a wide range of machine learning applications and methods to include deep learning (CNNs/RNNs), generative adversarial networks (GANS), model development, workflow automation, and training data set preparation.
Understanding/experience in mission and/or policy as it relates to National Security, Law Enforcement, National Defense, Homeland Security, Aviation/Space, and/or Public Health
TS/SCI preferred
Overview:
Noblis and our wholly owned subsidiary, Noblis ESI, are solving difficult problems that help our government and our country. We bring the best of scientific thought, management, and engineering expertise with a reputation for independence and objectivity. We support a wide range of government and industry clients in the areas of national security, intelligence, transportation, healthcare, environmental sustainability, and enterprise engineering. Learn more at Noblis -About Us

Why work at a Noblis company?
Our employees find greater meaning in their work and balance the other things in life that matter to them. Our people are our greatest asset. They are exceptionally skilled, knowledgeable, team-oriented, and mission-driven individuals who want to do work that matters and benefits the public.

Noblis has won numerous workplace awards. Noblis maintains a drug-free workplace and is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, veteran status or other characteristics protected by law.

Mastercard is looking for an energized commercial/technology attorney to join its dynamic legal team to serve as a legal partner for the recent acquisition, RiskRecon, which is part of the Cyber & Intelligence Solutions (C&I) group of Mastercard.

Mastercard’s C&I team provides strategic and cutting edge safety, security, identity and fraud solutions to Mastercard’s customers and cardholders.

This innovative team helps develop the next generation of Mastercard product solutions with respect to authentication, artificial intelligence, behavioral biometrics, cybersecurity, contactless transactions, and the internet-of-things.

Under the direction of the Senior Managing Counsel, Cyber & Intelligence Solutions, this position will provide the legal and general support for the global commercialization of the RiskRecon products and functionalities.

This position will be located in Purchase, NY and requires a background in cybersecurity.


Role

Provide solution-oriented counsel in support of the commercialization and sales efforts of the regional and local C&I teams;

Assist the broader C&I legal team by closely monitoring and staying tuned with C&I’s global and regional strategy and direction, connecting the dots and understanding big picture and helping to guide the rest of the legal team to support the business accordingly and assisting in keeping the legal team proactive and ahead;

Advise on legal, regulatory, reputational, and liability matters for new and existing products under an agile product development environment;

Provide subject matter expertise with respect to cybersecurity laws and product development;

Research on local law, conduct jurisdictional reviews, and collaborate with subject matter experts on data privacy, regulatory, IP, and other issues;

Structure, draft, and negotiate complex commercial, services, partnership and license agreements;

Leadership and liaison roles in aligning and collaborating across various business and legal teams;

Collaborate with team members on product development and go-to-market implementation;

Strategic partner and trusted advisor to a demanding business unit; High level of interaction with business clients;

Manage wide-ranging issues such as data usage/privacy, intellectual property, compliance, regulatory, and tax by partnering with subject matter experts in these areas and other stakeholder teams, and balancing these issues against reputational risk to ensure product constructs and commercial agreements are consistent with corporate strategy, internal policies and procedures and applicable laws and regulations;

Support sales and execution initiatives globally.


All About You

Strong global experience in cybersecurity as well as supporting commercialization of products and product management

Solid corporate transactional training and experience (preferably from a highly reputable law firm);

Must have strong drafting and negotiations skills with the ability to manage complex issues and deal structure;

Ability to operate in an agile and less than full information environment and ability to make quick but calculated decisions while managing risk effectively;

Must be pragmatic, solutions-oriented, business-friendly, creative, nimble, thought provoker, and an advocate for the business;

Must have leadership skills in bringing different perspectives together and work through competing priorities;

Must be able to work independently and collaboratively, but also take direction from manager and other team members, as appropriate;

Must multi-task effectively in an extremely fast-paced team environment with short turnaround times;

Must have strong communication skills to interact with clients and colleagues;

Must be a team player and willing to take on responsibilities and roles that support the team, region, department and the company;

Must be interested in significant contact with the business clients on a daily basis

A Juris Doctorate degree (or non-U.S. equivalent) and admitted to bar (or non-U.S. equivalent) and in good standing

Please note that this job description is not exhaustive and the job holder may be required to undertake additional duties from time to time to ensure the smooth running of the C&I business.
